comments: Hunter (ATL) establishes himself in Green's (HOU) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Mathews (HOU) moves alongside Young's (ATL) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Okongwu (ATL) rests a hand on Smith Jr.'s (HOU) shoulder and marginal contact occurs during the pursuit of the rebound.
Mathews (HOU) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Okongwu (ATL) prior to incidental follow-through contact occurring.
Hunter (ATL) reaches across and makes contact with Mathews' (HOU) body, which affects Mathews' SQBR during the drive.
Mathews (HOU) is moving alongside Young's (ATL) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together at the end of the drive.
Mathews (HOU) moves into and initiates contact with Young's (ATL) body, which affects his shot attempt near the basket.
Hunter (ATL) and Martin Jr. (HOU) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Collins (ATL) makes clean ball contact as Smith Jr. (HOU) secures the loose ball and marginal contact occurs as he slides his hand off of the ball during the rebound.
Hunter (ATL) brings his arm toward Porter Jr.'s (HOU) path and marginal contact occurs during Porter Jr.'s drive.
Hunter (ATL) legally contests Porter Jr.'s (HOU) jump shot attempt.
Murray (ATL) makes clean contact with the ball as he tries to dislodge the rebound from Smith Jr. (HOU) and any follow-through contact as Murray's hand slides off the ball is deemed marginal.
Green (HOU) initiates contact with Young's (ATL) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Martin Jr. (HOU) and Okongwu (ATL) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Murray (ATL) moves alongside Mathews' (HOU) path and absorbs the marginal contact when Mathews leans toward him during the driving shot attempt.
Hunter (ATL) establishes himself in Nix's (HOU) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Eason (HOU) legally contests Young's (ATL) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Young (ATL) commits a take foul on Nix (HOU).
Collins (ATL) establishes himself in Porter Jr.'s (HOU) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Mathews (HOU) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Porter Jr. (HOU) legally contests Collins' (ATL) jump shot attempt.
Griffin (ATL) commits a take foul on Mathews (HOU).
All Technical Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Nix (HOU) makes contact with Young's (ATL) arm prior to his gather, which affects his SQBR.
Murray (ATL) commits a take foul on Nix (HOU).
